name: parker-river-national-wildlife-refuge-narrative-report-january-february-march-and-april-19-ebef3
notes: This narrative report for Parker River National Wildlife Refuge outlines Refuge accomplishments from January through April of 1947. The report begins by summarizing the weather conditions and water conditions during this period. Wildlife- including migratory birds, upland game birds, big game animals, furbearers, predators, rodents, and raptors- is also covered. The Refuge development and maintenance section discusses physical developments and plantings. Resource management is outlined; topics include fur harvesting and timber removal. The public relations section of the report describes recreational uses, Refuge participation, Refuge visitors, and violations. N-R forms and photographs are attached.
